<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HB09194</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : AN ACT ESTABLISHING THE OVERSEAS FILIPINO WORKERS HOSPITAL AND APPROPRIATING FUNDS THEREFOR</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>ABSTRACT : Proposes to establish a national hospital facility with departmentalized clinical services and select specialty
care for OFWs and their families to fill in the gaps of paving better access and in providing higher quality of
healthcare.

Aims to provide comprehensive health care services to OWWA contributors and their legal dependents; conduct medical examinations to ensure the physical and mental capability of would-be OFWs; serve as primary referral hospital for repatriated OFW needing medical attention; generate relevant information and data for policy formulation; and participate in the health care provider networks and arrangements in accordance with Universal Health Care Act.
</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>MACAPAGAL ARROYO, GLORIA, TAN, ANGELINA &quot;HELEN&quot; D.L. M.D.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2019-05-21</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SIGNIFICANCE: NATIONAL</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>MOTHER BILL:&nbspHB09202</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON HEALTH ON 2019-05-22</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>SECONDARILY REFERRED TO THE COMMITTEE(S) ON APPROPRIATIONS</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO HEALTH on 2019-05-21;</td></tr></table>